PokÃ©mon Go , a hunt for health and happiness that pays off
it is fascinating to see the world changing .
many people have complained that teenagers and children no longer go out to play , but rather prefer to spend their free time on screens .
Pokemon Go is about getting people out of the sofa and getting more active .
the time on the screen was initially limited to the TV , then to video games and most recently to smartphones .
it is therefore great to see that technology and outdoor activities are not mutually exclusive .
I refer , of course , to the PokÃ©mon Go @-@ Wahn , an app based on the characters created for the video games in the 1990s ( later a cartoon series , game cards and other spin @-@ offs were created ) .
how many phenomena of pop culture sank interest before the release of the game in the USA , Australia and New Zealand in early July .
market entry in other countries has been delayed by the massive demand that the servers overloaded .
within days PokÃ©mon Go had more users than tinder and almost as many as Twitter .
how does it work ?
in short , players go out with their smartphones and look for pokÃ©mons that are followed with a GPS and can be &quot; photographed &quot; ( via a screenshot on the mobile phone ) or &quot; captured &quot; once they have been found .
a generation that played the game when it was younger joined the ballot and jumped out of the sofa .
in the US , the game led to a significant increase in steps that the &quot; average &quot; person departs every day .
Cardiogram , an app for Apple Watch , which follows 35,000 users , recently informed Washington Post that within two days of the launch of the game , the number of people who train 30 minutes each day jumped from 45 percent to 53 % .
the company does not know who is playing PokÃ©mon Go - it only sees the raw data to increase performance .
many public health awareness campaigns that people want to &quot; take 30 minutes , &quot; &quot; come from the sofa &quot; and &quot; be active every day &quot; came to deaf ears because many public messages on health are boring and come from people who look elastic .
however , the importance of sport cannot be overestimated .
those who regularly drive sport reduce their chances of cancer or depression .
physical activity helps with weight control , high blood pressure , diabetes and a long list of benefits that is too long to lead them here .
but the miracle of PokÃ©mon Go is that it causes people to do something outdoors that makes them fun .
so three pillars of health are covered - movement , fresh air and sunshine as well as fun .
some people even close new friendships in hunting .
as always , there are also Muslim players who have to complain about something .
and yes , someone could walk against a door .
what is to be done ?
there has been a breakthrough .
even if Smartphone apps like Fitbit were able to track our activity earlier , they gave us no reason to practice sport , as this game does .
the new will lose its appeal and use will decline over time .
however , due to Pokemon &apos;s success , there will be more games that will combine apps and virtual reality with action in the real world , helping many people to be more active , more fit and healthier .
