how to protect against weapons attacks with Krav Maga
the world outside is a dangerous place , but this video from Dailymail.com could make it a bit safer for you .
we talked to Rhon Mizrachi , a Grand Master of the Krav Maga Association in New York , to find out how to deal with armed robbers at a distance .
whether you are approaching you from the front or from the back , this video will show you how to turn the mirror around for your robber .
if you are approaching you from the back , you should first turn around so that you can see your attacker and &quot; get out of the shooting line , &quot; says Mizrachi .
then take the weapon between your forearm and your shoulder before beating it with your free elbow .
then hit him with his knees and turn away while the attacker cracks down from pain , throwing the gun out of his hands , throwing him in the face and moving backwards while turning the gun on him .
for attackers approaching from the front , the technique is similar - move your body out of the shutter line , take the weapon and turn it away so that the attacker cannot shoot .
at the same time , shift the weight to the weapon and hit the attacker on the chest , then turn the weapon out of its grip before moving backwards and turn the weapon on it .
sounds difficult ?
watch the video to see exactly how Mizrachi imagines .
but remember that it is the safest way to hand over your money to a robbery - unless you are a Krav Maga Grand Master .
