here comes the Enforcement Trailer
Germany &apos;s Raser has to adapt to the next generation of speed meters : in various federal states , including Hessen and Brandenburg , new flash devices are being tested , which are intended to be particularly effective in transmitting packets .
Vitronic &apos;s futuristic Enforcement Trailer from Wiesbaden , for example , can be used at accident points where it would be too dangerous for mobile measurement by the police .
for example , there is often no infrastructure needed to ensure that the speed limit is met with a stationary flash .
however , permanent mobile construction can be too dangerous or burdensome .
the Enforcement Trailer is self @-@ sufficient : its battery lasts five days in continuous measurement operation , the case data is transmitted encrypted via a modem .
laser measurement technology can also be used to track all vehicles across several tracks simultaneously .
variable speed limits and transit bans after time , driving tyres and vehicle class can also be monitored .
in high @-@ speed mode , the trailer can be moved with any car with a coupling .
so that it is not easy to clamp , it is lowered in the measuring operation so that the wheels disappear in the armoured and , incidentally , shaky outer case .
in addition , a built @-@ in alarm system is designed to protect the flash from vandalism .
since 2015 Vitronic &apos;s trailer has been tested and used in various federal states .
foreign authorities are also glittering with the new technology : France recently ordered 100 pieces , after ordering 150 pieces last year .
