steel - Light vision for the German steel industry
the crisis @-@ stricken and energy @-@ intensive German steel industry is being spared additional costs in millions .
financial burdens on the industry from green electricity production are on the table .
according to the Federal Minister of Economic Affairs , Sigmar Gabriel ( SPD ) of the &quot; Westdeutsche Allgemeine Zeitung &quot; ( WAZ , Fridays ) , the German General Newspaper ( WAZ ) .
&quot; I am really pleased that we have finally achieved this after two years of tough negotiations . &quot;
the European Commission had therefore initially planned to ask the steel producers who use gas from the furnace to produce electricity for their own consumption .
according to the German industry association , the steel industry threatened an additional cost of 120 to 240 million euros per year .
Gabriel said to the WAZ that there is now a basic agreement with the EU Commission after discussions with Competition Commissioner Margrethe Vestager .
only when the generators are replaced in the steel plants will an EEG charge of 20 percent .
but this is not the case in the steel industry either .
the IG Metals welcomed Germany &apos;s agreement with the EU Commission on the production of electricity .
the status quo of the current regime would thus be broadly established .
Gabriel &apos;s successful efforts for the steel industry were particularly important .
&quot; with regard to our &quot; Steel is Future &quot; campaign , this is a first step . &quot;
&quot; others must follow . &quot;
&quot; climate and employment targets also need to be weighed up in the reform of the emissions trading scheme , &quot; says IG Metal CEO JÃ¶rg Hofmann in Frankfurt .
the steel industry in Europe has suffered from overcapacity and considerable price pressure since the 2008 financial crisis .
last year , the situation continued to deteriorate as China &apos;s world &apos;s largest producer country , faced with weak domestic demand , threw steel on the world market .
European manufacturers accuse Chinese steel companies of price dumping .
during this spring , the situation has relaxed somewhat .
on the one hand , import duties imposed on imports have an effect on imports , and on the other , the economic outlook in China has deteriorated .
it is unclear how sustainable the price recovery is .
the German branch primary Thyssenkrupp remained cautious on Thursday .
finally , prices would have stagnated again .
the industry is responding to the difficult situation with further cost reductions .
ThyssenKrupp did not want to exclude the closure of individual works .
around 86000 people were employed in the German steel industry at the end of 2015 .
in July , German steel manufacturers remain cautious , despite rising prices and increasing orders .
at 3.4 million tonnes , they produced just six per cent less crude steel than in the previous month , as reported by the Steel Association on Friday .
after a short increase in May , the amount produced has now returned to the second month in a row .
since the beginning of the year , production has been two percent lower than the previous year .
the association expects an increase in output in the coming months thanks to an improved order situation .
community , spirit , health : good singing for seniors
the Singen has accompanied Ursel Kipp all her life : as a young girl she was in school choir , in Lehramt studies she taught music , and today the 78 @-@ year @-@ old sings in a senior choir .
&quot; singing moves me - emotional and physical , &quot; she describes .
after a sample she feels balanced , cheerful and more lively , she says .
by the way , she is doing her health and spirit a good job .
for Singen is a great hobby for seniors , says Erhard Hackler of the German Senior League .
most seniors sing in the choir and share the joy of music with like @-@ minded people , describes Hackler .
regular interaction allows seniors to establish and maintain social contacts .
because social and family structures often emerge at age , a choir is an ideal opportunity to spend time with other people .
this experience has also made Ursel Kipp in her choir : &quot; to deny and organize , to rely on the others and to learn from each other - a choir is a very special form of unity . &quot;
singing can be tough in a positive sense , says Hackler .
seniors train deep and controlled breathing .
those who regularly ask for their lungs do not get out of the purest so quickly in everyday life .
even when it comes to maintaining the sound of the voice at age , Singen is an ideal hobby .
Singen often has a very special effect on elderly people , says Ursula Lenz of the German Association of Senior Citizens &apos; Organisations .
in the older generations , common singing was much more important ; it was part of everyday life , both in school and in leisure time , explains it .
Lenz often observed that singing or listening to songs in older people arouses many memories , often combined with positive feelings of their youth .
through lyrics and melodies in particular , self @-@ dementia @-@ sufferers escape from long @-@ standing events .
in addition , when singing , a special performance is required for the head , explains Lenz .
at the same time , focus on one &apos;s own voice and on a given rhythm , adapting to the other singers - this is a great cognitive challenge .
older people who live alone practice not only focusing on themselves .
another positive aspect is the recognition of singing in the choir , says Hackler .
an enthusiastic audience is a great praise .
self @-@ esteem also grows through singing in the choir .
to show yourself : if I long for something , I will be better and more vigilant beyond me - this experience will be strengthened .
so there are good reasons to start singing .
if you want to try a new hobby , don &apos;t hesitate - even if you think you have little talent , let Lenz know .
you do not sing alone - 50 singing people , who is listening when a sound goes by ?
in search of the suitable offer senior citizens have different possibilities , says Hackler .
if someone sings from the audience in a senior choir , you can easily join .
many cities also offer views of the villages surrounding them .
if you want to sing in a church choir , you can contact the parish or church leader directly .
many senior citizens can also be found on the Internet .
anyone who does not have access to the Internet can ask the family , friends or neighbours for help with the Internet search .
if you want to sing , please join a choir , Hackler .
singing does well and has something liberating - that applies to all ages .
cats respond more sensitively than kittens to the horrors of young animals
biologists in Hanover have studied the effect of crying cat babies on adult animals .
to their surprise , the men were not cold either - but , unlike the females , they were always the same .
female cats can see the level of fatigue of cat babies when they mix the little ones .
they react 10 % faster to the sounds of kittens who are in great need , as scientists from the veterinary college and the Medical University of Hanover ( MHH ) found .
Kater also responds to kittens &quot; calls - but always the same .
&quot; obviously , the acoustic differences between miking less and heavily stimulated young animals are either unperceptible or not important for men , &quot; said the biologist Wiebke Konerding of MHH .
she is a dentist of the study published this Friday in the magazine &quot; BMC Evolutionary Biology . &quot;
in a previous study , the research team had already found that the duration and pitch of the kittens &apos; shrines are different from the urgency of their need for assistance .
a total of nine adult kittens and eight female kittens from MHH were observed .
they were played on the one hand by small boys who were taken out of the sausage box for three minutes and were separated by mother and siblings .
on the other hand , they were confronted with cries of more intense kittens , which were also raised .
researchers consider their results to be meaningful despite the small sample .
&quot; all females , even those who have not yet had their own young people , reacted differently to the horror , &quot; said Konerding .
they turned around faster to the loudspeaker when this call was played by the very rugged kittens .
this ability may be inclined or developed with gender maturity .
&quot; one surprise was that the men reacted at all , &quot; said the biologist .
in the past , scientists have already investigated the reactions of women and men to baby noise on several occasions in humans .
some studies showed that women were more sensitive to infants , whether they were mothers or not , reported the biologist Marina Scheumann .
