in the view of SteinhÃ¤user , the situation for these plants will continue to be precarious in the long term , especially as the Friesenbachtal wastewater treatment area cannot be extended by these plants because they are deficient facilities .
Bulgaria recorded inflation for the first time in 8 months
national statistics show that inflation in Bulgaria was 1 % on a monthly basis in July .
this is the highest value ( since June 2012 ) and the first above zero since October last year , when positive 0.2 % were recorded .
annual average inflation over the last 12 months ( August 2015 - July 2016 ) was -0.8 % compared to the previous 12 months ( August 2014 - July 2015 ) .
the consumer price index in July 2016 compared with June 2016 was 101.0 % , i.e. monthly inflation was 1.0 % .
inflation has been -0.2 % since the beginning of the year ( July 2016 compared with December 2015 ) and annual inflation in July 2016 was -0.2 % compared to July 2015 .
in July 2016 , compared with the previous month , prices rose among the following groups of consumer goods : food and non @-@ alcoholic beverages ( 1.7 % ) ; transport ( 1.8 % ) ; leisure and culture ( 6.3 % ) ; restaurants and hotels ( 1.2 % ) ; various goods and services ( 0.3 % ) .
prices fell for clothing and shoes ( 2.2 % ) ; furniture , household appliances and routine maintenance ( 0.5 % ) ; health ( 0.1 % ) .
prices remained unchanged as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco ; apartments , water , electricity , gas and other fuels ; communication and education .
