in the midst of the era of the Olympic Games , the Zen des Trampolins
wherever you are , however late it is , there are the Olympic Games .
the events in Rio de Janeiro feel constant and inevitable , a fast track between competition and ambition .
it is as if the Olympic torch was itself a burning stack , stretching from the bracelet to the swimmer to the triathlete .
you cannot turn on the TV , read a newspaper or listen to your neighbour in the queue in the coffee shop without hearing about Simone Biles , Katie Ledecky or the dispute between Michael Phelps and Chad le Clos .
and then there is Logan Dooley .
Dooley , who is for the first time at the Olympic Games and a women &apos;s swarm with horror , could well have been among these well @-@ known names that are sent to Prime Time , built by sponsors and good @-@ health TV advertising if he were a swimmer , turner or even a fan .
but Dooley , 28 , from Lake Forest , California , is fighting for gold in the Olympic trampoline .
the Olympic flame does not illuminate every event .
further from the centre , in some shadows there are sports that are not generally recognised : aerial pistol shooting , archery , badminton , taekwondo .
we will always have the chest swimming and may it prevail for a long time .
but if I may make modest arguments for my particular favorite , let me draw attention to the discreet charm of Trampolin .
although trampoline jumping has been an Olympic event since 2000 , when it had its debut in Sydney , it has been perceived so sparingly over the past 16 years that many people who I had asked did not know that it is an Olympic sport at all .
this could also be regional ignorance .
although the US sent athletes to compete , it has never won a medal in trampoline jumping , and by 2012 had an athlete who made it to the final .
the Chinese and Russians tend to share prices for men and the Chinese and the Canadians for women .
Dong Dong from China and Rosie MacLennan from Canada will defend their gold medal from London this year .
the trampoline jumping has a certain outside charm , partly because it sounds more suitable for the unenlightened ear for a clownsschool than for the Olympic Games .
at this point , I should admit that I am not an expert , but just an earth @-@ bound enthusiasm .
it has humoristic potential - the cartoonical quotation of its never @-@ ending cloudy impact - but also the grace of the turtle and diving , the two sports it essentially unites .
the word &quot; trampoline &quot; comes from the Spanish El Trampolin , which means &quot; jumping board . &quot;
rising winners jump on a gigantic trampoline , shoot almost up to 30 feet into the air , and must have a series of falling movements ( turning , lifting and saltos ) before they land on their feet .
according to the official Olympic programme , they are evaluated according to the performance , difficulty level and flight time .
two @-@ way athletes from 17 countries , 16 men and 16 women will compete in Rio .
the most common Olympic vector is straight .
medal @-@ hungry must go up and down in their quest for gold , faster , up and down , sometimes to the finish , sometimes back and forth , up and down in the playground .
they hunt not only the finish line or the starting wall , but also another cave @-@ like goal in television broadcasting : that of the world or the Olympic record .
the purposeful pursuit is noble , admirable , even fanatical - and it is enough to even throw a spectator into tears .
but it is also what I find somewhat arduous when watching these games .
the trampoline offers a respite .
the vector of the trampoline jumper is above .
a forward movement is not the goal .
he or she jumps up , seemingly heavy as an astronaut , then down , then effortlessly upwards .
here too there is competition , of course not without difficulty , but during the exercise there is no hectic attack on the goal , no wolves into the distance , only the dreamy , elegant lifting of time and gravity .
it is just as tough as competition can be at the Olympic Games .
women &apos;s qualifications and endings will be held on Friday afternoon , in streaming at 1.00 Eastern Time ; men &apos;s training sessions will also take place on Saturday at 1.00 p.m.
NBC will broadcast the endings as part of a afternoon block on both days from 14.00 .
amid the Olympia mania , they promise a quiet , nice moment , one that is likely to be overlooked in general .
