&quot; I believe what he says are legitimate , political comments , &quot; said Mr. Giuliani on the accuracy of Mr. Trump &apos;s statements about whether Mr. Obama and Mrs. Clinton had founded the Islamic State .
in this sense , it is true that before Obama ISIS was an almost unknown small organization , he called it backbenders , completely wrong , and it happened because he withdrew troops from Iraq .
most mainstream Republicans try to argue that Obama &apos;s administration , in which Mrs. Clinton served as Secretary of State , allowed ISIS to spread by refusing to aggressively control the situation in the Middle East .
before Friday &apos;s election campaigns in Pennsylvania , Mr. Trump continued his attacks on the media and accused them of being biased against each of his words .
he mocked the &quot; poor , distressing &quot; television experts who try to understand him and said , &quot; You can not ! . &quot;
some of the Democrats mocked Mr Trump &apos;s apology as yet another demonstration that he was unsuitable for the presidency .
