condoms with Chilipuder , fireworks promote Tanzania &apos;s elephant protection
nature defenders in Tanzania use an unorthodox way to prevent elephants from going into human @-@ inhabited settlements - they are throwing condoms on them filled with chilipuder .
the method has proved effective , and the Honeyguide Foundation , which had the idea of doing so years ago , has stepped up its support along with US nature conservation by training volunteers in villages in northern Tanzania to use a non @-@ violent four @-@ step method to protect their homes and harvesting without infringing animals .
previously , many spears used to defend themselves .
Friday is World Telephone Day dedicated to animal welfare .
&quot; since we developed the ... Toolkit , we have seen a change in attitudes within these communities , with much more confidence that they can dissuade the elephants from their fields without harming the elephants , &quot; Honeyguide Damian Bell said in a communication .
the first two steps include the illumination of the elephant with a torch and the bladder into a horn .
if he is not deterred , a so @-@ called &quot; chilicloud &quot; is thrown .
chilipuder mixes with earth together with a fireworks basket into a condom whose end is turned to the ignition .
when it is ignited , the condom bursts with a bang and spends fine dust on Chilipuder into the air .
a hat usually already out to hunt the elephant .
one last possibility is a shipyard that shoots a gold fire plant into the air , causing a loud , bright explosion .
