Lord Paul DÃ¤chton is Chairman of the Heathrow Board and former Commercial Secretary to the Treasury
adblock Plus , Facebook in the &quot; cat and mouse game &quot; on display blocking
for companies that make money with online advertising , one of the software manufacturers is trying to circumvent ad blocking , a &quot; cat and mouse game . &quot;
on Thursday , just two days after Facebook announced that it would block ad blockages on its desktop , Adblock Plus released a blog post in which it announced that users could update their filters in the program to block advertising on the social network again .
on Tuesday , Facebook announced that its desktop page would change the encoding of its ads to make it more difficult to recognize ads about which part of the page is advertising .
but Adblock announced that it found a new way to bypass the new codes .
in a Blogpost , Adblock Ben Williams &apos;s spokesman wrote that &quot; this kind of Hin and Her struggle between the timeless Open Source community and the bypasses has been underway since the invention of ad blockers , &quot; and that it is possible that Facebook will soon come up with a new solution .
the fact that the world &apos;s largest social media company has entered the fight is a strong indication of how worrying advertisers have become for the industry .
worldwide , according to a study carried out last year by Pagefair and Adobe , around 200 million people use ad blockers ; almost four times as much 2013 .
with 1.03 billion daily active users accessing Facebook via their mobile devices , mobile advertising accounts for 84 % of advertising revenue .
the company does not have an impact on Facebook &apos;s mobile app for the social network and Instagram .
advertising on desktop PCs represents a sufficient share of revenue , so Facebook seems to be worth investing such a move .
on Tuesday , Facebook announced that it would update its &quot; ad preference tool &quot; to give people more control over advertising targeted at them .
on Thursday , Facebook claimed that adblocks would be worrying about new filters , because they would block content on the site that is not advertising .
&quot; this is not a positive experience for users , so we plan to address the problem , &quot; said a Facebook spokesman in an email message .
ad blockers are a blunt means , so instead we have focused on development tools such as ad preferences to put more control in people &apos;s hands .
