restful Night : tips on sleep disorders
in the evening you walk eternally , at night you are waking up for hours , in the morning you can &apos;t think of sleep well before the wrestling .
that is far from recovering .
after all , such problems are in good society : according to the Robert Koch Institute , about a quarter of adults have sleep disorders and more than 10 % feel that their sleep is often or permanently unrecoverable .
how do sleep problems or sleep disorders arise ?
there are several forms of sleep disorders , and they can be based on a variety of causes , says Hans @-@ GÃ¼nter WeeÃ , member of the Executive Board of the German Society for Schlafforschung and Sleep Medicine .
however , what one understands by land is the insomnia , that is to say an intrusion and spill .
this is precisely what many people feel is unsatisfactory or insufficient , says Jens Wagenknecht , member of the Board of Directors of the German House Medical Association , with practice in Varel , Lower Saxony .
what is behind sleep disorders ?
the causes of sleep disorders are complex .
this can be based on organic , psychological or behavioral factors , but also on medicines .
often , sleep disturbance is an expression of another disease .
&quot; very early awakening is especially common in a depression , &quot; says WeeÃ .
and it may be that different factors are interdependent .
for example , if you have a tape discard , you can lie badly , wake up every two to three hours , and perhaps start to shake about everyday problems and concerns , you &apos;ll find your way .
this leads to tension and sleep is no longer possible .
when should I go to a doctor with sleep disorders ?
those who do not sleep well for a period of one month in at least three nights per week and who are affected by the day should go to the doctor , advise WeeÃ .
the impairment may look very different : one is locked , tired , unloaded , has difficulties with attention and concentration , is slightly irritable , has mood fluctuations or physical complaints such as stomach or headache .
to relieve sleep disturbances , it is important to find out their causes .
treatment options include behavioural changes , cognitive behavioural therapy , or even drugs - classic sleeping pills only in exceptional cases and for a maximum of two weeks .
established sleeping mediators hardly exist in Germany , emphasizes Prof. Ingo Fietzen , head of the interdisciplinary slaughterhouse of the CharitÃ© UniversitÃ¤t Medizin Berlin .
therefore , in case of sleep problems , you should first contact the doctor , advise WeeÃ .
it can investigate whether the problems have a physical cause .
who should go to the sleeping laboratory and what happens ?
for example , medical doctors recommend using snoring with respiratory agents , with sickening daily fatigue , sleeping transmitters , or if you don &apos;t find the cause of a breakdown , Fietzen explains .
it is not really necessary to prepare for the investigation .
you should spend the day normally .
&quot; just don &apos;t take lunch sleep , &quot; says Fietze .
after strolling , you go to bed at its normal time .
in addition to the electrodes on the body , you carry a nose glasses , a breast belt and a fan on your finger .
moreover , a camera on the ceiling captures the sleeping ends .
how can people get to grips with the problems ?
there are quite a lot of position screws on which you can start a better sleep .
it is important to note that regular sleep and rest periods , not too long in bed , do not sleep in the day , do not watch TV to sleep , avoid alcohol and watch out for the clock at night - then you start to expect immediately , and that is completely unhelpful .
