new containers will soon be on WasenstraÃe
it has been a serious problem for some time to find housing for the connecting refugees that have been recognised .
local authorities are responsible for the connection .
they must accommodate refugees in their own or rented homes .
the costs for the construction , rent or renovation of these accommodation must be borne by the municipalities themselves .
responsibility varies from country council to community and job center .
problem : there are free objects , but not every landlord wants to offer his apartment .
the search has been very difficult for some time .
in fact , the administration does not find private housing .
so far , it has not worked , but it depends on private apartments , says Deuschle .
therefore , communal housing must be seized , as it is so beautiful .
so new containers will soon be installed in WasenstraÃe .
but only apartments are not enough .
perspective is the keyword , Regine customer and Annika Deuschle agree .
in addition to permanent jobs , they are traineeships , training places , school places , one @-@ euro jobs and relief activities for refugees and migrants who need to be frozen or set up .
&quot; more seats would be good , &quot; says Regine customer .
many work in the Bauhof or help house managers , do non @-@ profit work - and that is motivated and very orderly , as Annika Deuschle reports .
it hopes that work for the community will have a positive external impact .
that is &quot; no employment therapy . &quot;
however , activity is not just work .
the day needs a fixed structure , say Deuschle and customer .
people should develop a sense of belonging .
so there is a need for sports , contacts with locals and , above all , language courses .
professional courses are rar .
so here too , administration and honorary officials are involved .
it is central that refugees feel that they are welcome and welcome in Germany .
the long duration of proceedings is a problem .
they must explain to refugees that it takes time and that they can reasonably bridge the gap , for example with language courses .
anyone who at some point feels that he can help no one in Urbach should not work , and that he will never integrate .
the clear majority is motivated .
however , there are also problems , customers say honestly , &quot; people who don &apos;t work at all . &quot;
all this is already a &quot; mammoth task . &quot;
a difficult question : are the two , following recent events , afraid of radicalisation , including in a small community like Urbach ?
&quot; no , &quot; Regine customer says very clearly , &quot; what some might call naÃ¯ve . &quot; a residual risk could and would not exclude it .
but the helpers are already aware .
these incidents were also the subject of refugees .
they would fear that the attackers would completely discredit them .
&quot; they want to show that they have nothing to do with this , &quot; says Regine customer .
many would like to stay in Urbach .
so primary and honorary officials on the ground and in the region must look for activities .
they always have a background in which a new shock to refugees and migrants could soon come to Urbach .
does Germany need a ceiling ?
to answer this question clearly , politics is afraid .
in fact , it is unfair to put them on the ground .
&quot; we have not yet arrived in Urbach where we want to go , &quot; says Annika Deuschle .
no new refugees , that would ease the situation .
